  "prompt": "What does it mean if you are vomiting white foam?",
  "response": "Vomiting white foam can be concerning and may indicate various underlying conditions. Here are some potential causes:\n\n1. **Acid Reflux or Gastritis**: Stomach acid mixed with mucus can produce white foam. Conditions like acid reflux, gastritis, or GERD (gastroesophageal reflux disease) could be the culprit.\n\n2. **Excess Saliva or Mucus**: Sometimes, excessive saliva or mucus in the stomach, especially if you haven\u2019t eaten in a while, can lead to vomiting white foam.\n\n3. **Pancreatitis**: Inflammation of the pancreas can cause vomiting, which may include white foam, often accompanied by severe abdominal pain.\n\n4. **Bile Reflux**: If bile flows back into the stomach, it can mix with stomach contents and lead to vomiting foam, though this is often yellow or green.\n\n5. **Esophageal Issues**: Problems with the esophagus, such as esophageal spasms or strictures, can cause white foam vomiting.\n\n6. **Respiratory Issues**: Conditions like bronchitis, pneumonia, or severe coughing can lead to vomiting mucus, which may appear as white foam.\n\n7. **Toxin Poisoning**: Ingestion of certain toxins or chemicals can cause irritation of the stomach lining, leading to vomiting foam.\n\n8. **Ketoacidosis**: In people with diabetes, ketoacidosis (a serious complication of high blood sugar) can cause nausea and vomiting, which may include white foam.\n\n9. **Postnasal Drip**: Excessive mucus from conditions like sinusitis can drip into the stomach and lead to vomiting foam.\n\n10. **Gallbladder or Liver Issues**: Problems with the gallbladder or liver, such as gallstones or hepatitis, can sometimes cause vomiting of foam.\n\n### When to Seek Medical Attention:\n- If vomiting persists for more than 24 hours.\n- If vomiting is accompanied by severe pain, fever, or signs of dehydration.\n- If you suspect poisoning or have ingested a harmful substance.\n- If you have other concerning symptoms like dizziness, confusion, or blood in the vomit.\n\nIt\u2019s important to consult a healthcare professional to determine the exact cause and receive appropriate treatment.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
